class_notes: Online with synchronous sessions TBD. On campus intensives TBD.
course_description: This course builds upon evaluation and management of patients across the lifespan in pre-hospital, urgent and emergency care settings. Emphasis on evidence-based practice, clinical decision making, team skills, advanced practice competencies in emergency preparedness and response.
prerequisites: NRSG 756D as prerequisite, NRSG 806D and NRSG 807D as co-requisites, or equivalent transfer credit.
